body:
@marcphilipp Just want to make sure I got it right, so the proposal is to extend the API and give the possibility to the user of `Assertions` to specify which exception should be thrown by the `assertTimeoutPreemptively`?

So it would be something like:

```java
class Assertions {
  
    ...

    public static <T> T assertTimeoutPreemptively(Duration timeout, ThrowingSupplier<T> supplier,
			Supplier<String> messageSupplier, Throwing throwing) {
	return AssertTimeout.assertTimeoutPreemptively(timeout, supplier, messageSupplier, throwing);
    }

    public enum Throwing {
        ASSERTION_EXCEPTION,
        TIMEOUT_EXCEPTION
    }
    
     ...

}
```
